attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the paper stack and the black and white page. The student places the black and white page back on the table, keeps the paper stack and proceeds to open the paper support of the printer. The student pulls out the paper support and then closes it back. The instructor asks the student to pull out the paper support and keep it that way by pushing it backward, which the student does. The student puts the paper stack on the paper support, removes it to align it and then puts it back. The student slides the blue tab to align the paper stack to the right. The student erroneously pulls the bottom front part of the printer and the instructor corrects him. The student pulls and, eventually, opens the tray. He also slides open the tray extension. The student grabs the black and white page, opens the copy gate and places the page on the laser scanner of the printer. Before closing the copy gate, the student align the page to the bottom left corner of the laser scanner. The student approaches the copy button, hesitates and decides to press the resume button. The instructor asks the student to cancel the job and the student presses the cancel button. The student presses the copy button and waits for the copy to be ready. The student removes the copy from the printer and places it on the table. The student opens the copy gate, takes the black and white page, removes it from the printer and, after closing the copy gate, places it on the table. The student grabs the new  ink cartridges from the table, inspects the cartridge gate of the printer and opens it. The student puts the new ink cartridges on the table and removes the color ink cartridge from the printer. The student takes the new color ink cartridge and inserts it on the printer. The student removes the black ink cartridge from the printer and places it on the table. He takes the new black ink cartridge and tries to insert but fails to do so. The instructor asks the student to flip the cartridge. The student takes out the ink cartridge flips it and inserts it back on the printer before closing the cartridge gate. The student moves away the old ink cartridges and closes the tray extension and tray of the printer. The student slides the blue tab to the left, removes the paper stack and puts it on the table. Finally, the student closes the paper support of the printer.
